race.comment: CALL ME FROSTY (4) showed talent as a juvenile during a 2-start winter campaign, and resumed with a game effort for third at Ascot a fortnight ago, finishing half a length from the winner. He will be spot on for this far easier assignment, and is the one to beat. BOSUN (2) hit the line hard on debut when finishing third and less than a length from the winner, after racing greenly around the final bend. He will be better for the experience, and should go close to taking this out. SATIN BOW (6) resumed from a spell as a much stronger mare, and ran her best race yet, finishing third. She has a superior gate this time, and has each-ay claims again. SHE'S HOT (8) tackled G3 company in his final run as a juvenile, and has looked in good condition at the trials, finishing close up in the most recent of those. William Pike takes the ride, and from the pole position, she will be hard to hold out. FIELD MISTRESS (9) drops back to 1200m, and is ready to figure in the top 3. Stick with her.
